ModernDive data frames

Chester Ismay

This page provides an interactive way to view the data frames used in the ModernDive textbook. You can click on the Chapter the specific data frame is introduced in the floating Table of Contents. The specific package the data frame is included in is provided as a secondary header.

These interactive data tables were created using the DT R package.
For data frames larger than 100 rows, the data has been split onto multiple pages for ease of use. For data frames larger than 10,000 rows, a random sample of size 10,000 of the data is selected instead.
